# Frontend RRG (Reactive Reliability Gate)

## When This Rule Applies
When editing files under `app/` or `shared/components/`.

## Critical Rules
- **No direct window mutation** in component code except one-time registration: `window.X = { ... }`, `window.X = function ...`, or `window.X = X` (same identifier). Any other `window.* =` is a violation.
- **No `innerHTML` assignment** in components (XSS and reactivity bypass).
- **State**: use Vue reactivity or store (core/state, messages store); mutations only via defined setters.

## Refactor on edit
When editing a block that contains outdated reactivity (disallowed window mutation, innerHTML, duplicated state), attempt to rewrite it per RRG. Skip if refactor would require large scope or break dependencies. Skill: id:sk-d4f8a2 (app/skills/rrg-refactor-on-edit.md).

